{"author":{"id":"4f963a0d76ce6c39f97104052558e06c993d1b814af553b854df7a1c5e9a35f1"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1742217442,"nonce":"xgxLLvTg9IIINKyOCvGGkT9h4rQ=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOAW4Y0s6uWOJu","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/6856","origin":"github"},"title":"repeatmasker package corruption after post-link.sh","message":"Hello,\n\nThe repeatmasker package comes with a dummy `Dfam.h5` file, cf [build.sh](https://github.com/bioconda/bioconda-recipes/blob/729d87ac5c862116e723cb6293fa69fbc32fe8f6/recipes/repeatmasker/build.sh#L21).\nUpon installation, [post-link.sh](https://github.com/bioconda/bioconda-recipes/blob/729d87ac5c862116e723cb6293fa69fbc32fe8f6/recipes/repeatmasker/post-link.sh#L8) will download the complete database (55 GB) and replace the file.\n\nThe problem we're seeing is that when Conda is able to use hard-links, the `Dfam.h5` file in the environment is the same as in the package itself, meaning that `post-link.sh` is modifying the package cache !\n\nIt makes further conda commands like `conda install repeatmasker=4.1.5` throw this message:\n\n```\nSafetyError: The package for repeatmasker located at /software/treeoflife/conda/miniconda/pkgs/repeatmasker-4.1.5-pl5321hdfd78af_1\nappears to be corrupted. The path 'share/RepeatMasker/Libraries/Dfam.h5'\nhas an incorrect size.\n  reported size: 68 bytes\n  actual size: 5861387976 bytes\n```","files":null}]}